13 (8) Beginning January 1, 2027, and each year thereafter, the
14 department shall adjust the monetary thresholds under subsections
15 (1), (2), and (6) by an amount determined by the state treasurer to
16 reflect the cumulative annual percentage change in the Consumer
17 Price Index. As used in this subsection "Consumer Price Index"
18 means the annual average Consumer Price Index for All Urban
19 Consumers (CPI-U), all items in U.S. city average, reported by the
20 Bureau of Labor Statistics of the United States Department of Labor
21 or its successor or, if the index is discontinued, an equivalent
22 index reported by a federal authority. If no such index is
23 reported, Consumer Price Index means the substitute index chosen by
24 the state treasurer.
